Jeanette Chabalala, News24(Supplied to News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Bloemfontein &ndash; A man sustained minor injuries when a train collided with his truck at a railway crossing outside Bloemfontein on Thursday afternoon, paramedics said. &nbsp;ER24 paramedics found the truck partially wrapped around the front of the locomotive, spokesperson Russel Meiring said.&nbsp;The driver was flung from the vehicle on impact. Parts of the truck were scattered around the scene. Nobody in the train was injured.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.